cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CC

This paper deals with the analysis of natural language and artificial language using multifractal methods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves statistical analysis, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of Cantor sets and binomial cascades indicates the involvement of discrete structures, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves the comparison of two languages, which could suggest the involvement of artificial intelligence, placing it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of correlations, which could suggest the involvement of computational complexity, placing it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
